    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Standing Desk Converter in 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 6+ models</div>

      <p>Sitting all day damages your back, your circulation, and your focus. But replacing a whole desk costs hundreds of dollars and a full afternoon of assembly. A standing desk converter sits on your existing desk and lifts your monitor and keyboard to standing height in seconds — giving you the health benefits of standing without throwing away furniture you already own.</p>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 6 standing desk converters based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For stability we assessed frame design, base dimensions, and lift mechanism specifications. For height range we evaluated manufacturer-published minimum and maximum height specifications. For weight capacity we assessed published ratings and lift mechanism specifications.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Lift range, weight capacity, and stability at full height</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Frame rigidity, gas spring longevity, and surface durability</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to full standing desks and other converters</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Assembly effort, lift force, and keyboard tray ergonomics</li>
      </ul>

