      </table>

      <h2 id="best-overall">Best Overall: FlexiSpot Standing Desk Converter</h2>
      <p>The FlexiSpot Standing Desk Converter won on the strength of its gas spring lift, which raises 35 pounds of monitor and keyboard from 4.5 inches to 19.7 inches with one hand. There is no cranking, no awkward two-handed heave, and no sudden drop — the lift is smooth and holds at any height in the range. According to the manufacturer, the gas spring is rated for sustained use without weakening, even at maximum load.</p>
      <p>The 28-inch wide surface is what makes this converter genuinely usable for real work. It fits a 27-inch monitor and a 24-inch monitor side by side, with room left for a laptop. Cheaper converters top out at 24 inches and force you to choose between a second monitor and a laptop. The removable keyboard tray sits at a separate, lower level, which keeps your wrists straight whether you are sitting or standing — a detail that three of the six converters in our comparison got wrong.</p>
      <p>The zero-assembly design is the final reason it ranks first. It arrives flat in a box, unfolds in under five minutes, and is ready to use immediately. The VIVO budget pick also recommended requires 30 minutes of screwing and bolting, which matters if you hate furniture assembly. The FlexiSpot also folds flat for storage or transport, which no full standing desk can do.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>FlexiSpot Standing Desk Converter</h2>
        <ul>
